Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveThe Kogi State governor, Yahaya Bello, on Saturday, declared his interest in the Presidency ahead of the 2023 general elections.
He officially declared at the Eagle Square in Abuja.

Bello also picked Hafsat Abiola-Costello, daughter of the presumed winner of the June 1993 presidential election, late Moshood Abiola, as his presidential campaign Director-General.
